One of the harmonically folding boards was then broken by a cable about three feet [1 m] long.
To avoid further injury, the board was not opened.
The astronauts were originally tasked with making a control walk off the Discovery spacecraft and then repairing another failed rotor system solar panel, but instead had to devote their full time to repairing the damaged solar panel.
Scott Parazynski was chosen to perform the stunt, suspended from a 100-foot robotic arm attached to the station's spacecraft mast.
He's one of the best spacewalkers at NASA.
He's tall, strong, extremely skilled, muscular upper body and long arms.
