What kind of insurance is right for me?
Motor insurance, which provides protection for the owner of the vehicle against various types of damage, is a significant expense and also depends on several factors such as age, gender, date of licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured and nature of use.
Buying a car is just the first step.
In fact, choosing the right insurance policy is often more difficult than deciding what kind of car to buy.
First, we need to know what's going on.
Motor insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement took the form of an insurance contract stipulating that the insurance company would pay compensation in the event of the event of damage in return for a fixed premium.
The premium is basically the amount paid for insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors such as age, gender, date of license, marital status, type of car to be insured, use of the car, etc.
Insurance companies determine premiums on the basis of statistics, i.e. the higher the risk of an accident, the higher the premium.
That's why people over 25 or women pay less, because statistics show that they're less at risk because they're more careful.
Similarly, insurance companies have concluded from the data that married people also cause fewer accidents than single people.
Frequency is key for the type of car you use.
More frequent use increases the risk of an accident.
When setting the premium, insurance companies take into account a number of factors.
Therefore, the owner should look carefully to select the most appropriate form of insurance for his profile.
The following are the most important factors to consider when choosing a policy to best suit your insured's needs and provide an acceptable price.
When taking out insurance, people under 25 have to take into account a number of disadvantages, such as lack of driving experience and recent driving licences.
While it is ideal to have insurance against all hazards, there are more economical solutions.
More careful drivers can take out a full auto insurance policy, which will protect them from all dangers and will make the price affordable.
In this type of contract, the insured pays part of the damage.
"The amount of premium paid by the insured depends on the premium; the higher the premium, the lower the premium", says Luis Noguera, head of First Europa, an online insurance broker in Spain.
Another option is third party extended liability insurance, where the customer insures himself against damage caused to others but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, you will be insured against theft, fire damage and loss of the car.
That's good advice.
If you are under 25, be careful and avoid accidents if possible, as this will affect your bonus and reduce your future payments.
The bonus is the discount on the basic rate of the insurance company.
The penalty for a loss of the basic tariff is called a malus.
"The amount of the bonus and the bonus depends on the insurance company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonus rate", explains Noguera.
Once they are over 25, it is easier for owners to take out adequate insurance, since the risk of accidents is reduced by experience gained over the years.
We recommend that you take out a full insurance policy.
"Young people are often not yet able to apply their experience properly in an accident, even when driving", says the director of a European insurance company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when drivers have overcome the fear of beginners.
If you are already married but have no children, it is best to take out comprehensive insurance, if your financial circumstances allow.
Insurance companies consider married couples with children to be the least risky customers, and therefore the premium they pay is lower.
In this case, it is best to have a full insurance policy (up to EUR 300) or, if you have a higher bonus, to cover damage to another person from the third year of the vehicle.
"They drive more comfortably, but they also have more purchasing power and can afford to pay more for their own use", says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, full insurance with a deductible (around EUR 150) is recommended, or liability insurance can be added if the bonus is higher.
Car insurance is very important, not only because it provides protection for the owner in the event of accidents but also because it is a big expense, so it is essential to choose the right form of insurance that is tailored to you.
