The German Dax rose by 2.6%, while the French CAC40 rose by 2.3%.
Credit market turmoil was renewed after a highly demanded auction organised by the European Central Bank sold three-month-old bonds to European banks at a price of 4.7 percent, a record since April 2001.
With the UK's interbank interest rate, Libor, hitting its highest level since September at 6.59 percent after a steady rise since November 12, the Bank of England is under increasing pressure to follow the Fed and the ECB and to add additional capital to the London financial market.
