"We have initiated a number of reforms in primary schools since the first Pisa study", said a spokesman for the Ministry of Education.
So the government introduced comparative tests nationwide.
To get kids to start school early, the last year of kindergarten is free, a model that other states have started to copy.
Whether or not this improvement in student performance is lasting will be determined only by future comparative studies.
According to a 2003 Pisa survey, the percentage of students at risk has dropped from 29 percent to 20 percent.
The Saarland's overall performance, however, did not improve as much as that of the other Länder.
Bavarians are more calculating.
The Saar countrymen are most upset that the Pisa survey does not take foreign language skills into account - otherwise they would be harvesting beans in this area anyway.
The language of the neighbouring countries is a compulsory subject in secondary schools, even if the Saarlanders are not French speakers.
